_B-Roll-_Visitor_Activities_%2853943125753%29.jpg/1280px-Acadia_B-Roll-_Visitor_Activities_%2853943125753%29.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/37/Acadia_B-Roll-_Visitor_Activities_%2853943125753%29.jpg","cap":"Acadia B Roll Visitor Activities (53943125753)","desc":"Clips featuring people of all ages hiking, enjoying scenery, kayaking and canoeing, and taking photos against scenic backdrops.","credit":"National Park Service · Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Acadia_B-Roll-_Visitor_Activities_(53943125753).jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Acadia_B-Roll-_Peaks_and_Scenery_%2853942874226%29.jpg/1280px-Acadia_B-Roll-_Peaks_and_Scenery_%2853942874226%29.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c2/Acadia_B-Roll-_Peaks_and_Scenery_%2853942874226%29.jpg","cap":"Acadia B Roll Peaks and Scenery (53942874226)","desc":"A series of clips featuring mountains, forests, and water viewed from above.","credit":"National Park Service · Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Acadia_B-Roll-_Peaks_and_Scenery_(53942874226).jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/40/Acadia_B-Roll-_Visitor_Crowds_%2853943210049%29.jpg/1280px-Acadia_B-Roll-_Visitor_Crowds_%2853943210049%29.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/40/Acadia_B-Roll-_Visitor_Crowds_%2853943210049%29.jpg","cap":"Acadia B Roll Visitor Crowds (53943210049)","desc":"Clips showing coastlines, parking lots, and urban areas that have large crowds of people and lines.","credit":"National Park Service · Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Acadia_B-Roll-_Visitor_Crowds_(53943210049).jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cf/Acadia_Porcupine_-_Flickr_-_Chris_Jackolski.jpg/1280px-Acadia_Porcupine_-_Flickr_-_Chris_Jackolski.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/cf/Acadia_Porcupine_-_Flickr_-_Chris_Jackolski.jpg","cap":"Acadia Porcupine Flickr Chris Jackolski","desc":"Acadia National Park, Sieur de Monts. Thanks for the Explore! This juvenile porcupine was on the side of a carriage road in the park, just eating. Another group of hikers had seen it before me. Then, a bigger group of tourists came by, and a ranger asked from afar, \"Is that what I think it is?\" I nodded \"Yes\", but now I think she was probably asking whether it was a bear.","credit":"Chris Jackolski · CC BY-SA 4.0","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Acadia_Porcupine_-_Flickr_-_Chris_Jackolski.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/Magaret_Todd_schooner_wide_Acadia_National_Park_August_2015.jpg/1280px-Magaret_Todd_schooner_wide_Acadia_National_Park_August_2015.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/24/Magaret_Todd_schooner_wide_Acadia_National_Park_August_2015.jpg","cap":"Magaret Todd schooner wide August 2015","desc":"Wide shot of the schooner Margaret Todd in the Mt. Desert Narrows, Bar Harbor, ME. August 2015.","credit":"Thudfinger · CC BY-SA 4.0","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Magaret_Todd_schooner_wide_Acadia_National_Park_August_2015.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f6/Bar_Island_%28Maine%29.jpg/1280px-Bar_Island_%28Maine%29.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/f6/Bar_Island_%28Maine%29.jpg","cap":"Bar Island (Maine)","desc":"Bar Island, an uninhabited tidal island in Bar Harbor, Maine. It's part of the Acadia National Park.","credit":"Quintin Soloviev · CC BY 4.0","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Bar_Island_(Maine).jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2d/Schoodic_Scenic_Byway_-_Clamming_Along_the_Schoodic_Byway_-_NARA_-_7722022.jpg/1280px-Schoodic_Scenic_Byway_-_Clamming_Along_the_Schoodic_Byway_-_NARA_-_7722022.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/2d/Schoodic_Scenic_Byway_-_Clamming_Along_the_Schoodic_Byway_-_NARA_-_7722022.jpg","cap":"Clamming Along the Schoodic Byway","desc":"A visitor searches for some of Maine's famous clams along the shore. Location: California Status: Public domain. Photo by James H. Fisher of Hancock County Planning Commission","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Schoodic_Scenic_Byway_-_Clamming_Along_the_Schoodic_Byway_-_NARA_-_7722022.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/36/Schoodic_Scenic_Byway_-_Looking_Down_a_Black_Dike_at_Schoodic_Head_-_NARA_-_7722018.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/36/Schoodic_Scenic_Byway_-_Looking_Down_a_Black_Dike_at_Schoodic_Head_-_NARA_-_7722018.jpg","cap":"Looking Down a Black Dike at Schoodic Head","desc":"This cavity in the rocks at Schoodic Head forms a black dike which has been worn away by the ocean. Location: Winter Harbor, Maine Status: Public domain. Photo by David Kennedy","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Schoodic_Scenic_Byway_-_Looking_Down_a_Black_Dike_at_Schoodic_Head_-_NARA_-_7722018.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/4f/Schoodic_Scenic_Byway_-_Schoodic_Education_and_Research_Center_-_NARA_-_7722045.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/4f/Schoodic_Scenic_Byway_-_Schoodic_Education_and_Research_Center_-_NARA_-_7722045.jpg","cap":"Schoodic Education and Research Center","desc":"The Schoodic Education and Research Center, also known as the Rockefeller House, was once a Navy base and is now on the National Register of Historic Places. Location: Maine Status: Public domain. Photo by James H. Fisher of Hancock County Planning Commission","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Schoodic_Scenic_Byway_-_Schoodic_Education_and_Research_Center_-_NARA_-_7722045.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikiped